cholarships    UIC Connection    Contact Us    UIC menu    UIC.edu    Campus Map       Search                        Assessment Committee     View Menu  Down arrow icon            Breadcrumbs   STUDENT AFFAIRS    About    Student Affairs Assessment    Assessment Committee        Student Affairs Assessment Committee  The Student Affairs Assessment Committee was established in 1997. The Committee facilitates a variety of research and assessment activities and initiatives within the Division of Student Affairs.  The Student Affairs Assessment Committee is charged with the following tasks:   Provide guidance and advisory support to the OVCSA on assessment of programs and services.  Offer a more in-depth understanding of UIC students through data collection focused on student engagement, learning, satisfaction, and climate.  Discuss and disseminate assessment findings within Student Affairs and to interested persons in the campus community.  Summarize assessment and research literature relevant to the operation and effectiveness of Student Affairs.   STUDENT AFFAIRS ASSESSMENT COMMITTEE MEMBERSHIP LIST   Nick Ardinger, Campus Housing Paula Benton-Pierce, AAAN Christine Corral, Career Services Jose DeLeon, ACE Sladjana Grbic, Campus Programs Ana Hoban, International Services Bernard Little, Student Development Services Jason Maslanka, Digital Services Lynne Thompson, Campus Recreation Jill Rothamer, The UIC Experience program Julie Wren/Lance Kennedy Phillips, Office of Institutional Research (Ex-Officio) Annette Wright, Dean of Students  Chair: Mark Manderino, OVCSA          About    Back to main content           Senior Leadership    Department Directors    Office Staff    Giving Opportunities     Online Giving Form      Strategic Priorities    Student Affairs Assessment     Annual Report    Assessment and Planning Model    Assessment Committee    Assessment Resources    Reports of Interest    Student Affairs Learning Outcomes      Social Media    Contact Us     Feedbac